ees/1412-9bda3377/tests/src/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.79.Final/src/test/java/io_netty/netty_common/Netty_commonTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage io_netty.netty_common;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nclass Netty_commonTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void test() throws Exception {\\n        System.out.println(\\\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\\\");\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_7\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,240p' /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1412-9bda3377/post-gen-interventions/io.netty_netty-common_4.1.79.Final.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nCodex fixed the metadata-related failures for `io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final`, but the native test run still failed on two generated tests that exercise runtime behaviors not caused by missing reachability metadata.\\n\\nRemoved generated tests:\\n- `src/test/java/io_netty/netty_common/PlatformDependent0_5Test.java`\\n- `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/platform-dependent0-5-test/reflect-config.json`\\n- `CleanerJava6Test.leavesHeapBufferUntouchedWhenFreeingThroughPlatformDependentCleaner()` from `src/test/java/io_netty/netty_common/CleanerJava6Test.java`\\n\\n## Failure analysis\\n\\n### 1. `PlatformDependent0_5Test.locatesDirectBufferConstructorFromPrivilegedAction()`\\n\\nRoot cause: **not metadata-related**.\\n\\nThe test mutates `Integer.TYPE` through `sun.misc.Unsafe` to force Netty's privileged action down a legacy constructor-discovery path, then expects that mutation to be observable and restorable at runtime. In the native image run, the mutation does not remain visible: the restore step sees `int.class` instead of the injected `long.class` and fails with `expected: <long> but was: <int>`.\\n\\nThis is a runtime/JDK-internals behavior issue in native image, not a missing reflection/resource/JNI registration problem. The test depends on rewriting a fundamental JDK primitive-type field, which is not a stable assumption for this environment.\\n\\nBecause the only extra generated test-only file for this test was `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/platform-dependent0-5-test/reflect-config.json`, that file was removed as well.\\n\\n### 2. `CleanerJava6Test.leavesHeapBufferUntouchedWhenFreeingThroughPlatformDependentCleaner()`\\n\\nRoot cause: **not metadata-related**.\\n\\nThe test tries to simulate an older Netty cleaner configuration by changing system properties, then calls `PlatformDependent.freeDirectBuffer()` on a heap buffer and expects a no-op. In the native image run, Netty still ends up in `io.netty.util.internal.CleanerJava9.freeDirectBuffer()`, which delegates to `Unsafe.invokeCleaner`. That JDK API rejects heap buffers and throws `java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Not a direct buffer`.\\n\\nThis shows the failure is caused by native-image/runtime selection of cleaner behavior rather than missing metadata. Additional metadata would not make `Unsafe.invokeCleaner` accept a heap buffer.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support is still valuable because Codex already resolved the actual metadata gaps that were blocking other tests. The metadata-fix log explicitly shows that the metadata-related failures were fixed and that the run improved from four failing tests to these two non-metadata failures.\\n\\nAfter removing only the non-metadata tests above, the library test suite passes with:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final --stacktrace`\\n\\nThat means the generated metadata and the remaining generated tests continue to validate real Netty native-image support for this version, and only the environment-specific false negatives were trimmed.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1412-9bda3377/tests/src/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.79.Final/build.gradle\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1412-9bda3377/tests/src/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.79.Final/build.gradle\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\nplugins {\\n    id \\\"org.graalvm.internal.tck\\\"\\n}\\n\\nString libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\\n\\ndependencies {\\n    testImplementation \\\"io.netty:netty-common:$libraryVersion\\\"\\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\\n}\\n\\n<<<<<<< HEAD\\ntasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\\n    jvmArgs += [\\n        \\\"--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED\\\",\\n        \\\"--add-opens=java.base/java.nio=ALL-UNNAMED\\\",\\n        \\\"--add-opens=java.base/jdk.internal.ref=ALL-UNNAMED\\\",\\n        \\\"--add-exports=java.base/jdk.internal.misc=ALL-UNNAMED\\\"\\n    ]\\n}\\n\\n=======\\n>>>>>>> b7fd45d621 (Scaffold io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final)\\ngraalvmNative {\\n    agent {\\n        defaultMode = \\\"conditional\\\"\\n        modes {\\n            conditional {\