chmark suites.\\n- Keep metrics data separate from the main codebase for easier analysis and history tracking.\\n\\n## Layout\\n\\n```console\\nmetadata-forge-metrics/\\n├─ script_run_metrics/\\n└─ benchmark_run_metrics/\\n```\\n\\n### `script_run_metrics/`\\n\\nStores metrics from regular script runs in `metadata-forge`.\\n\\n- Each AI script has a `JSON` file named after the script.\\n- Each object in the `JSON` will represent metrics of one run for a single library version.\\n- Example:\\n  - `script_run_metrics/new_library_support.json` – metrics for a script that manages or tests adding new library support.\\n\\n### `benchmark_run_metrics/`\\n\\nStores metrics from predefined benchmark configurations.\\n\\n- Each benchmark has a JSON file named after it.\\n- Example:\\n  - `benchmark_run_metrics/metadata_entries_hunter.json` – metrics for a benchmark suite that tracks performance or behavior when adding new library support, using a strategy that favors generating tests which tend to cover as many metadata entries as possible.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_25\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \\\"test_generation_failed|success_with_intervention|metadata_fix_failed|remaining failures|improved from 4 failing tests to 2|<<<<<<<|>>>>>>>\\\" /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/logs/add-new-library-support/io.netty_netty-common_4.1.79.Final/*.log /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/logs/post-gen/io.netty_netty-common_4.1.79.Final/*.log /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/logs/metadata-fix/io.netty_netty-common_4.1.79.Final/codex.log /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1412-9bda3377/tests/src/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.79.Final/build.gradle /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1412-9bda3377/tests/src/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.79.Final/user-code-filter.json /home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_wor