    \\\"library\\\": \\\"io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final\\\",\\n2666-    \\\"starting_commit\\\": \\\"b7fd45d62110e575ad3ae98a042f571d5b4303b8\\\",\\n2667-    \\\"ending_commit\\\": \\\"d56e06a1a5393f9fbe9087ff31544cadcf12f7ef\\\",\\n2668-    \\\"strategy_name\\\": \\\"dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\\\",\\n2669-    \\\"agent\\\": \\\"pi\\\",\\n2670-    \\\"model\\\": \\\"oca/gpt-5.5\\\",\\n2671-    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success_with_intervention\\\",\\n2672-    \\\"stats\\\": {\\n2673-      \\\"version\\\": \\\"4.1.79.Final\\\",\\n2674-      \\\"dynamicAccess\\\": {\\n2675-        \\\"breakdown\\\": {\\n2676-          \\\"reflection\\\": {\\n2677-            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.925,\\n2678-            \\\"coveredCalls\\\": 37,\\n2679-            \\\"totalCalls\\\": 40\\n2680-          },\\n2681-          \\\"resources\\\": {\\n2682-            \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 0.833333,\\n2683-            \\\"coveredCalls\\\": 5,\\n2684-            \\\"totalCalls\\\": 6\\n2685-          }\\n--\\n2695-          \\\"ratio\\\": 0.096745,\\n2696-          \\\"total\\\": 47041\\n2697-        },\\n2698-        \\\"line\\\": {\\n2699-          \\\"covered\\\": 1143,\\n2700-          \\\"missed\\\": 9965,\\n2701-          \\\"ratio\\\": 0.102899,\\n2702-          \\\"total\\\": 11108\\n2703-        },\\n2704-        \\\"method\\\": {\\n2705-          \\\"covered\\\": 301,\\n2706-          \\\"missed\\\": 2707,\\n2707-          \\\"ratio\\\": 0.100066,\\n2708-          \\\"total\\\": 3008\\n2709-        }\\n2710-      }\\n2711-    },\\n2712-    \\\"post_generation_intervention\\\": {\\n2713-      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"metadata_fix_failed\\\",\\n2714-      \\\"intervention_file\\\": \\\"post-gen-interventions/io.netty_netty-common_4.1.79.Final.md\\\",\\n2715:      \\\"analysis_markdown\\\": \\\"# Post-generation intervention report\\\\n\\\\nLibrary: io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final\\\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\\\n\\\\n## Summary\\\\n\\\\nCodex fixed the metadata-related failures for `io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final`, but the native test run still failed on two generated tests that exercise runtime behaviors not caused by missing reachability metadata.\\\\n\\\\nRemoved generated tests:\\\\n- `src/test/java/io_netty/netty_common/PlatformDependent0_5Test.java`\\\\n- `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/platform-dependent0-5-test/reflect-config.json`\\\\n- `CleanerJava6Test.leavesHeapBufferUntouchedWhenFreeingThroughPlatformDependentCleaner()` from `src/test/java/io_netty/netty_common/CleanerJava6Test.java`\\\\n\\\\n## Failure analysis\\\\n\\\\n### 1. `PlatformDependent0_5Test.locatesDirectBufferConstructorFromPrivilegedAction()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: **not metadata-related**.\\\\n\\\\nThe test mutates `Integer.TYPE` through `sun.misc.Unsafe` to force Netty's privileged action down a legacy constructor-discovery path, then expects that mutation to be observable and restorable at runtime. In the native image run, the mutation does not remain visible: the restore step sees `int.class` instead of the injected `long.class` and fails with `expected: <long> but was: <int>`.\\\\n\\\\nThis is a runtime/JDK-internals behavior issue in native image, not a missing reflection/resource/JNI registration problem. The test depends on rewriting a fundamental JDK primitive-type field, which is not a stable assumption for this environment.\\\\n\\\\nBecause the only extra generated test-only file for this test was `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/platform-dependent0-5-test/reflect-config.json`, that file was removed as well.\\\\n\\\\n### 2. `CleanerJava6Test.leavesHeapBufferUntouchedWhenFreeingThroughPlatformDependentCleaner()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: **not metadata-related**.\\\\n\\\\nThe test tries to simulate an older Netty cleaner configuration by changing system properties, then calls `PlatformDependent.freeDirectBuffer()` on a heap buffer and expects a no-op. In the native image run, Netty still ends up in `io.netty.util.internal.CleanerJava9.freeDirectBuffer()`, which delegates to `Unsafe.invokeCleaner`. That JDK API rejects heap buffers and throws `java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Not a direct buffer`.\\\\n\\\\nThis shows the failure is caused by native-image/runtime selection of cleaner behavior rather than missing metadata. Additional metadata would not make `Unsafe.invokeCleaner` accept a heap buffer.\\\\n\\\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\\\n\\\\nThe remaining generated support is still valuable because Codex already resolved the actual metadata gaps that were blocking other tests. The metadata-fix log explicitly shows that the metadata-related failures were fixed and that the run improved from four failing tests to these two non-metadata failures.\\\\n\\\\nAfter removing only the non-metadata tests above, the library test suite passes with:\\\\n\\\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-common:4.1.79.Final --stacktrace`\\\\n\\\\nThat means the generated metadata and the remaining generated tests continue to validate real Netty native-image support for this version, and only the environment-specific false negatives were trimmed.\\\"\\n2716-    },\\n2717-    \\\"metrics\\\": {\\n2718-      \\\"input_tokens_used\\\": 1386977,\\n2719-      \\\"cached_input_tokens_used\\\": 17691648,\\n2720-      \\\"output_tokens_used\\\": 154298,\\n2721-      \\\"iterations\\\": 33,\\n2722-      \\\"cost_usd\\\": 54.9265,\\n2723-      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 691,\\n2724-      \\\"tested_library_loc\\\": 1143,\\n2725-      \\\"metadata_entries\\\": 32,\\n2726-      \\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 10.29\\n2727-    },\\n2728-    \\\"artifacts\\\": {\\n2729-      \\\"test_file\\\": \\\"tests/src/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.79.Final/src/test/java/io_netty/netty_common/ResourcesUtilTest.java\\\",\\n2730-      \\\"metadata_file\\\": \\\"metadata/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.79.Final/reachability-metadata.json\\\"\\n2731-    }\\n2732-  },\\n2733-  {\\n2734-    \\\"timestamp\\\": \\